1
00:01:10,182 --> 00:01:11,525
You’re flying on the same flight as us, aren’t you, Auntie?

2
00:01:11,525 --> 00:01:13,552
I don’t even know which plane it is, dear.

3
00:01:13,552 --> 00:01:15,259
Don’t worry, we’ll take care of you.

4
00:01:15,259 --> 00:01:16,852
Sappé sattā...

5
00:01:16,852 --> 00:01:18,359
Auntie...

6
00:01:18,359 --> 00:01:19,991
Sorry, but you can’t chant out loud here.

7
00:01:19,991 --> 00:01:20,583
Boy!

8
00:01:20,583 --> 00:01:22,177
You can’t use that.

9
00:01:22,177 --> 00:01:23,008
I'l go ahead and lie down.

10
00:01:23,008 --> 00:01:23,757
That's good for you!

11
00:01:23,757 --> 00:01:25,257
I got a bed ready and everything.

12
00:01:25,788 --> 00:01:29,136
Madam! That Peck woman from Glam’s crew, she tried to shoot us!

13
00:01:29,136 --> 00:01:30,847
Siri, get my weapons ready.

14
00:01:30,847 --> 00:01:32,279
Glam, get your ass out here right now!

15
00:01:32,279 --> 00:01:33,911
Do you even know him? Why are you after him?

16
00:01:33,911 --> 00:01:35,459
I said let go!

17
00:01:35,459 --> 00:01:36,854
That’s enough, Madam!

18
00:01:36,854 --> 00:01:39,854
This woman, Porn, will no longer be his victim anymore.

19
00:01:44,721 --> 00:01:48,148
I don’t think that’s a good idea.

20
00:01:48,148 --> 00:01:50,262
I really can’t do it.

21
00:01:50,262 --> 00:01:53,616
What if someone walks in and hears?

22
00:01:53,616 --> 00:01:55,616
No need to be tense. Just relax.

23
00:02:02,490 --> 00:02:05,317
Whoa! Madam Porn, what is this?

24
00:02:05,317 --> 00:02:07,222
You really brought a massage boy into the office?

25
00:02:07,222 --> 00:02:08,936
Massage boy, my ass.

26
00:02:08,936 --> 00:02:11,936
This is Mr. Wang. He’s my fortune teller today.

27
00:02:13,006 --> 00:02:16,599
How would I know? He does look the part.

28
00:02:16,599 --> 00:02:19,099
Do I really look that much like a massage boy?

29
00:02:21,506 --> 00:02:24,421
So, what kind of reading are we doing here?

30
00:02:24,421 --> 00:02:26,254
Why does it have to be a secret?

31
00:02:26,254 --> 00:02:28,600
This Mr. Wang isn’t just any fortune teller.

32
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:31,600
He’s a sneeze psychic.

33
00:02:34,108 --> 00:02:37,216
Oh wow, Madam, you really dig up the weirdest stuff.

34
00:02:37,216 --> 00:02:38,216
Alright. Let’s begin.

35
00:02:44,888 --> 00:02:46,359
Madam, are you okay?

36
00:02:46,359 --> 00:02:48,188
Go on, sneeze.

37
00:02:53,311 --> 00:02:55,066
From the sound of that sneeze,

38
00:02:55,066 --> 00:02:59,059
though bold, it carries a faint gentleness.

39
00:02:59,059 --> 00:03:03,059
Toward the end, there’s a nasal whistle.

40
00:03:03,565 --> 00:03:06,041
A sneeze like that means...

41
00:03:06,041 --> 00:03:13,041
you’re destined for misfortune, with sky-high stubbornness,

42
00:03:13,832 --> 00:03:16,832
but no matter what you do, you’ll crash and burn. I rest my case.

43
00:03:18,861 --> 00:03:21,861
Excuse me, is this a psychic or a sound analyzer?

44
00:03:23,136 --> 00:03:25,605
So what should I do then?

45
00:03:25,605 --> 00:03:29,605
What will help shift your fate is changing your sneeze.

46
00:03:30,595 --> 00:03:34,595
The new sneeze must be smaller in sound,

47
00:03:34,861 --> 00:03:36,492
but still powerful.

48
00:03:36,492 --> 00:03:37,166
Okay.

49
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:39,166
Try sneezing like me.

50
00:03:49,122 --> 00:03:50,122
Like this?

51
00:03:50,873 --> 00:03:54,874
So if I change my sneeze, things will get better?

52
00:03:55,940 --> 00:03:57,851
If only it were that easy.

53
00:03:58,368 --> 00:04:00,515
Then why make her do it in the first place?

54
00:04:00,515 --> 00:04:03,709
Because it can help improve her luck.

55
00:04:03,709 --> 00:04:07,178
But if you really want to shift your destiny,

56
00:04:07,178 --> 00:04:11,178
then the time has come to shed your old self

57
00:04:11,686 --> 00:04:14,113
and fight with your true face.

58
00:04:14,113 --> 00:04:18,113
Shed my old self. Fight with my true face.

59
00:04:27,896 --> 00:04:30,896
Siri, it’s really dusty in here.

60
00:04:32,047 --> 00:04:33,047
Yes.

61
00:04:41,558 --> 00:04:44,352
Ooh, those earrings are cute! Are they new?

62
00:04:44,352 --> 00:04:45,347
They look great!

63
00:04:45,347 --> 00:04:46,347
You're really on point today.

64
00:04:50,766 --> 00:04:54,766
Where the hell is that big bird?

65
00:04:54,822 --> 00:04:58,538
My eyes aren’t what they used to be. I'm getting old!

66
00:04:58,538 --> 00:05:00,538
Why is it like this?

67
00:05:04,085 --> 00:05:05,715
Everything’s just blurry now.

68
00:05:05,715 --> 00:05:07,715
I guess I need new glasses again.

69
00:05:10,747 --> 00:05:13,455
Ah, this is a bit better.

70
00:05:13,455 --> 00:05:16,968
Hello, Auntie, can I help you with anything?

71
00:05:16,968 --> 00:05:18,155
Yes, dear. Could you check something for me?

72
00:05:18,155 --> 00:05:22,155
I don’t even know which plane I’m getting on!

73
00:05:22,428 --> 00:05:25,383
Could I please see your boarding pass?

74
00:05:25,383 --> 00:05:28,014
Did I mess something up, sweetie?

75
00:05:28,014 --> 00:05:30,804
I mean your boarding pass, your plane ticket.

76
00:05:30,804 --> 00:05:33,190
Well, why didn’t you just say plane ticket, huh?

77
00:05:33,190 --> 00:05:35,106
You scared me, I thought I’d messed up big time!

78
00:05:35,106 --> 00:05:40,106
Here, here, here, take a look for me, will you?

79
00:05:43,764 --> 00:05:46,397
Auntie, is this a boarding pass...

80
00:05:46,397 --> 00:05:48,159
or a blueprint for an industrial factory?

81
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:49,830
Why is it this huge?

82
00:05:49,830 --> 00:05:52,777
You wouldn’t understand, dear. You're not old yet.

83
00:05:52,777 --> 00:05:55,206
I had them print it extra large.

84
00:05:55,206 --> 00:05:56,840
My eyes aren’t what they used to be.

85
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:59,388
Oh! Auntie’s on the same flight as us!

86
00:05:59,388 --> 00:06:01,702
We’ll take care of you, Auntie.

87
00:06:01,702 --> 00:06:02,929
You can wait here for now.

88
00:06:02,929 --> 00:06:04,921
Thank you, sweetheart, thank you.

89
00:06:04,921 --> 00:06:07,315
It’s rare to meet young folks

90
00:06:07,315 --> 00:06:09,349
who actually care about the elderly.

91
00:06:09,349 --> 00:06:10,345
Take good care of me, okay?

92
00:06:10,345 --> 00:06:10,902
Of course.

93
00:06:10,902 --> 00:06:12,729
I’m counting on you.

94
00:06:12,729 --> 00:06:15,077
Girls, are you two flight attendants?

95
00:06:15,746 --> 00:06:16,932
Yes, we are.

96
00:06:16,932 --> 00:06:20,932
So they don’t check faces anymore when hiring flight attendants?

97
00:06:27,683 --> 00:06:31,683
Oh dear, sweetie, what happened to your face?

98
00:06:32,431 --> 00:06:36,432
Did you get hit by flying sparks while they were fixing the plane or something?

99
00:06:36,704 --> 00:06:38,737
I knew it!

100
00:06:38,737 --> 00:06:40,812
Does it hurt, baby? Does it hurt?

101
00:06:40,812 --> 00:06:44,079
My face has always looked like this, Auntie.

102
00:06:44,079 --> 00:06:46,026
You're hugh, sweetie.

103
00:06:46,026 --> 00:06:48,463
You eat a lot, don't you?

104
00:06:48,463 --> 00:06:50,329
I eat clean, actually.

105
00:06:50,329 --> 00:06:50,882
Eat clean?

106
00:06:50,882 --> 00:06:51,750
Yes, Auntie.

107
00:06:52,258 --> 00:06:55,695
Yeah, I’ve seen lots of people say that. Eating clean.

108
00:06:55,695 --> 00:06:58,322
Eat too many veggies and you end up like a hippo.

109
00:06:58,322 --> 00:07:01,078
Or a buffalo. Or an elephant, you know.

110
00:07:01,078 --> 00:07:02,387
But hey, at least, you're healthy.

111
00:07:03,379 --> 00:07:04,726
Yes. I'm strong and healthy.

112
00:07:04,726 --> 00:07:07,798
Tell me, do you girls have boyfriends?

113
00:07:07,798 --> 00:07:11,788
Judging by your faces, probably not, huh?

114
00:07:11,788 --> 00:07:13,656
We only have fans, Auntie.

115
00:07:13,656 --> 00:07:17,008
So the youth these days date ghosts or something?

116
00:07:17,008 --> 00:07:19,160
Hey you, did you get your nose done?

117
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,549
Yes, I did.

118
00:07:20,549 --> 00:07:24,549
Then why didn’t you get the rest of your face done too, dear?

119
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:30,051
If it were me, I’d fix the whole thing in one go!

120
00:07:30,558 --> 00:07:32,558
I'm so happy talking to you, girls.

121
00:07:41,349 --> 00:07:43,024
Well, well. Look who finally showed up, All-New, Kreetha!

122
00:07:43,024 --> 00:07:45,214
I thought you two were dead already.

123
00:07:45,214 --> 00:07:47,248
Madam, that Peck woman,

124
00:07:47,248 --> 00:07:48,636
from Glam’s crew,

125
00:07:48,636 --> 00:07:50,624
she tried to shoot us.

126
00:07:50,624 --> 00:07:52,221
This time she was really going for the kill.

127
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:54,214
But luckily, Peck’s younger sister showed up just in time.

128
00:07:54,214 --> 00:07:55,925
Otherwise, I wouldn’t be standing here telling you this.

129
00:07:55,925 --> 00:07:57,711
Unbelievable. That’s too much.

130
00:07:57,711 --> 00:07:58,777
You mean Glam, right?

131
00:07:58,777 --> 00:08:00,777
I meant you. Running to mommy, huh?

132
00:08:03,086 --> 00:08:04,314
Also, Madam...

133
00:08:04,314 --> 00:08:07,662
Sky knows we’ve been digging into Glam.

134
00:08:07,662 --> 00:08:08,732
That means...

135
00:08:08,732 --> 00:08:12,733
the people at Glamorous Airline probably know who we are now.

136
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,870
I don’t think so, Madam.

137
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:17,817
Sky doesn’t seem very bright.

138
00:08:17,817 --> 00:08:19,565
I doubt she figured anything out.

139
00:08:19,565 --> 00:08:20,312
Are you sure?

140
00:08:20,312 --> 00:08:22,783
Positive, Madam.

141
00:08:22,783 --> 00:08:26,783
Glam...don’t you think you've gone too far this time?

142
00:08:27,658 --> 00:08:29,367
If you want to play dirty,

143
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:32,119
then I won’t hold back anymore.

144
00:08:32,119 --> 00:08:37,228
The time has come...for me to shed my old self

145
00:08:37,228 --> 00:08:40,729
and fight with my true face.

146
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:42,719
Madam, is your blood pressure okay?

147
00:08:42,719 --> 00:08:45,719
Are you about to pass out? Take your meds first.

148
00:08:47,746 --> 00:08:51,017
Do you think this is a joke, Siri?

149
00:08:51,017 --> 00:08:52,212
What's yellow?

150
00:08:52,212 --> 00:08:53,561
Maybe it's a pill or a hair gel for your dad’s head!

151
00:08:53,561 --> 00:08:54,549
Okay…you're not in the mood for jokes now.

152
00:08:54,549 --> 00:08:56,304
You all better listen closely.

153
00:08:56,304 --> 00:09:00,257
From this moment on, I’m the one who’s hunting Glam.

154
00:09:00,257 --> 00:09:01,810
And I won’t stop

155
00:09:01,810 --> 00:09:05,357
until Glamorous Airline burns to the ground right before my eyes.

156
00:09:05,357 --> 00:09:07,192
And let it be known...

157
00:09:07,192 --> 00:09:11,192
this woman, Porn, will no longer be his victim anymore.

158
00:09:11,385 --> 00:09:12,980
Siri.

159
00:09:12,980 --> 00:09:15,173
Prepare my weapons.

160
00:09:15,173 --> 00:09:17,122
Madam! Whoa, slow down! Where are you going?

161
00:09:17,122 --> 00:09:19,274
Let’s talk about this first!

162
00:09:19,274 --> 00:09:21,274
You can’t stop me. Get out of my way!

163
00:09:23,862 --> 00:09:27,377
Damn, what did she eat? She’s strong like a bull.

164
00:09:27,377 --> 00:09:30,692
Siri, quit complaining and go after Madam, hurry!

165
00:09:30,692 --> 00:09:32,692
Madam Porn! Wait for me!

166
00:09:36,958 --> 00:09:39,108
Looks like the beast mode of Mom is back.

167
00:09:39,108 --> 00:09:40,735
Well, they're all gone now.

168
00:09:40,735 --> 00:09:42,735
Are you waiting for your Dad to cut a ribbon or something, All-New? Move it!

169
00:09:49,203 --> 00:09:50,989
Where should we go for the long weekend?

170
00:09:51,699 --> 00:09:53,689
I wanna go to Korea.

171
00:09:53,689 --> 00:09:54,762
How about Japan instead?

172
00:09:54,762 --> 00:09:57,671
Japan or Korea, you can go for free!

173
00:09:57,671 --> 00:10:01,107
Because Found&Found is celebrating its one-year anniversary!

174
00:10:01,107 --> 00:10:03,740
Fly for free and shop 'til you drop in Japan and Korea

175
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:07,531
with the Found Shop Fin in JK campaign!

176
00:10:07,531 --> 00:10:10,446
All you have to do is spend 690 baht

177
00:10:10,446 --> 00:10:12,234
at Found&Found,

178
00:10:12,234 --> 00:10:15,145
and you’ll get a chance to win a free trip to Japan or Korea!

179
00:10:15,145 --> 00:10:19,145
Plus, there are 111 e-voucher prizes up for grabs...

180
00:10:19,181 --> 00:10:22,094
worth over two million baht!

181
00:10:22,094 --> 00:10:22,686
Let's buy it.

182
00:10:22,686 --> 00:10:23,686
Buy out the whole place!

183
00:10:26,916 --> 00:10:27,916
Glam!

184
00:10:28,190 --> 00:10:30,186
Glam, I know you’re around here.

185
00:10:30,186 --> 00:10:32,660
Come out now. I’m here!

186
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:36,161
Madam, let’s just go back. He’s not around here.

187
00:10:36,161 --> 00:10:39,392
Oh, please. I always see his people around here.

188
00:10:39,392 --> 00:10:43,188
In that case, they must be at the office.

189
00:10:43,188 --> 00:10:44,988
Let’s go. We’re storming their headquarters!

190
00:10:49,498 --> 00:10:52,250
Finally, the day has come.

191
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:55,165
The day I no longer have to hide who I am.

192
00:10:55,165 --> 00:10:58,113
Glam, where are you? Come out.

193
00:10:58,113 --> 00:11:01,184
Glam! Glam! Come out!

194
00:11:01,184 --> 00:11:02,857
Glam, where are you?

195
00:11:02,857 --> 00:11:04,645
Don’t go hiding here.

196
00:11:04,645 --> 00:11:06,156
Come out and face me!

197
00:11:06,156 --> 00:11:08,989
Tid-Gift, get behind me!

198
00:11:08,989 --> 00:11:10,785
Auntie?

199
00:11:10,785 --> 00:11:12,262
How did you get in here?

200
00:11:12,262 --> 00:11:15,652
Well, if the door’s open, why wouldn’t I come in?

201
00:11:15,652 --> 00:11:17,652
Hey, this aunt looks familiar.

202
00:11:20,089 --> 00:11:21,402
It’s Pam!

203
00:11:21,402 --> 00:11:23,037
Pam, the one we met at the bar!

204
00:11:23,037 --> 00:11:23,870
Right.

205
00:11:23,870 --> 00:11:26,462
Etch this into your cerebrum, all of you.

206
00:11:26,462 --> 00:11:30,256
My name is Madam Porn, not Pam.

207
00:11:30,256 --> 00:11:31,842
Pam...

208
00:11:31,842 --> 00:11:34,232
Madam, what are you doing here?

209
00:11:34,232 --> 00:11:37,179
I came here looking for your boss.

210
00:11:37,179 --> 00:11:38,446
Where is Glam?

211
00:11:38,446 --> 00:11:42,446
Glam, come out right now! You, you Glam!

212
00:11:43,473 --> 00:11:46,183
I know you’re watching me.

213
00:11:46,183 --> 00:11:48,096
Look me in the eye.

214
00:11:48,096 --> 00:11:52,049
I’m Madam Porn. I’m here now. Come out!

215
00:11:52,049 --> 00:11:56,049
Auntie, this is getting serious. You're talking to a CCTV camera.

216
00:11:56,637 --> 00:11:58,034
And how is Glam supposed to know what you’re saying?

217
00:11:58,034 --> 00:11:59,780
Why wouldn’t he?

218
00:11:59,780 --> 00:12:01,780
The camera’s broken.

219
00:12:03,367 --> 00:12:04,876
So what?

220
00:12:04,876 --> 00:12:07,470
You! Go get Glam for me right now!

221
00:12:07,470 --> 00:12:09,306
Mr. Glam isn’t here.

222
00:12:09,306 --> 00:12:12,574
How do you even know him? What brings you here?

223
00:12:12,574 --> 00:12:16,574
You think I’m stupid and don’t know who you people are?

224
00:12:16,845 --> 00:12:20,350
Tid-Gift, the wild little party girl.

225
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:24,350
And Chai, the Casanova, multiple conquests in one night.

226
00:12:25,341 --> 00:12:27,088
And where are the rest of your friends?

227
00:12:27,088 --> 00:12:30,358
Sky. Chaba. Come out right now!

228
00:12:30,358 --> 00:12:31,033
Wait a sec.

229
00:12:31,033 --> 00:12:33,388
How the hell does she know so much about us?

230
00:12:33,388 --> 00:12:36,017
Exactly. How does she know all this?

231
00:12:36,017 --> 00:12:40,018
How do I know so much about Glamorous Airline?

232
00:12:40,564 --> 00:12:44,194
Because I

233
00:12:44,194 --> 00:12:45,464
have...

234
00:12:51,183 --> 00:12:52,013
Whoa, calm down, Auntie!

235
00:12:52,013 --> 00:12:53,685
Who are you calling Auntie? Let go of me!

236
00:12:53,685 --> 00:12:54,394
That’s enough, Auntie.

237
00:12:54,394 --> 00:12:58,224
Let me go right now! I said let go!

238
00:12:58,224 --> 00:13:01,059
Tid-Gift, are you okay?

239
00:13:02,650 --> 00:13:03,716
Still holding up?

240
00:13:03,716 --> 00:13:05,409
Good. I’m not done yet.

241
00:13:05,409 --> 00:13:06,081
Let go! Let me go!

242
00:13:06,081 --> 00:13:07,553
That’s enough!

243
00:13:07,553 --> 00:13:10,221
Siri! Where’s the gun I told you to bring?

244
00:13:10,221 --> 00:13:11,489
Get it out right now!

245
00:13:11,489 --> 00:13:12,595
I didn’t bring it, Madam.

246
00:13:12,595 --> 00:13:14,428
Please don’t do this. I’m begging you.

247
00:13:14,428 --> 00:13:15,542
I’ll even ordain for you if that’s what it takes.

248
00:13:15,542 --> 00:13:18,255
Siri, when we get back, you’re dead meat.

249
00:13:18,255 --> 00:13:22,049
Let go! Let me go!

250
00:13:22,049 --> 00:13:23,077
Let go!

251
00:13:23,077 --> 00:13:24,866
Hello, Mr. Wang?

252
00:13:24,866 --> 00:13:27,137
Madam Porn says she’ll pay you an extra hundred thousand

253
00:13:27,137 --> 00:13:29,250
if you just say "Stop it, Porn. Today’s not an auspicious day."

254
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:30,559
“Fighting today will only lead to loss and more loss.”

255
00:13:30,559 --> 00:13:31,559
Got that? Deal.

256
00:13:33,475 --> 00:13:35,825
Stop it, Porn. Today’s not an auspicious day.

257
00:13:36,163 --> 00:13:39,163
Fighting today will only lead to loss and more loss.

258
00:13:41,353 --> 00:13:43,225
Wow, you really are superstitious.

259
00:13:43,225 --> 00:13:45,225
A million voices don’t compare to one line from a fortune teller.

260
00:13:48,462 --> 00:13:50,002
Let’s go, Madam.

261
00:13:50,002 --> 00:13:52,187
Chai, Tid-Gift, leave the rest to me.

262
00:13:52,187 --> 00:13:53,187
Yeah. I’m counting on you, All-New.

263
00:14:01,898 --> 00:14:04,898
Why does it have to be this high up?

264
00:14:10,485 --> 00:14:11,485
Well, this works out just fine.

265
00:14:15,753 --> 00:14:19,753
Excuse me, Auntie. Sorry, but this is actually my seat.

266
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:20,970
Your seat?

267
00:14:20,970 --> 00:14:23,121
Well, I got here first, so I sat here first, girl.

268
00:14:23,121 --> 00:14:25,432
There are plenty of empty seats. Just pick another one, sweetie.

269
00:14:25,432 --> 00:14:27,502
But this one’s assigned to me, Auntie.

270
00:14:27,502 --> 00:14:28,614
Yeah, but I got here first.

271
00:14:28,614 --> 00:14:31,330
So what if you did? This is still my seat.

272
00:14:31,330 --> 00:14:33,439
Wow, this girl really doesn’t understand human language.

273
00:14:33,439 --> 00:14:35,267
So many seats and she wants to fight over this one.

274
00:14:35,267 --> 00:14:37,220
Is there a problem here?

275
00:14:37,578 --> 00:14:39,134
Explain it to her! I got here first.

276
00:14:39,134 --> 00:14:41,329
I sat here. And now she’s trying to take it from me.

277
00:14:41,329 --> 00:14:44,321
Look! So many empty seats and she picks this one. Isn’t that odd?

278
00:14:44,321 --> 00:14:46,708
Um, Auntie, the thing is...

279
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:49,977
It’s a rule that everyone has to sit in their assigned seat.

280
00:14:49,977 --> 00:14:52,684
Doesn’t matter who got here first. Everyone must sit in their assigned seat.

281
00:14:52,684 --> 00:14:55,191
She still doesn’t get it. Explain it again.

282
00:14:55,191 --> 00:14:56,906
Tell her I was here first, so I sat here!

283
00:14:56,906 --> 00:15:00,782
Yes, but everyone must sit in the seat they were assigned.

284
00:15:00,782 --> 00:15:02,934
As per the ticket, Auntie.

285
00:15:02,934 --> 00:15:03,481
Really?

286
00:15:03,481 --> 00:15:04,430
Yes.

287
00:15:04,430 --> 00:15:07,380
Alright then, girls. Tell me where you want me to sit.

288
00:15:07,380 --> 00:15:09,380
May I please see your boarding pass again, Auntie?

289
00:15:12,492 --> 00:15:16,492
Why, girl? I'm old, can’t you just let me sit here?

290
00:15:16,642 --> 00:15:17,315
You’re making such a fuss over nothing.

291
00:15:17,315 --> 00:15:18,466
We're not.

292
00:15:18,466 --> 00:15:20,215
This ticket was expensive, you know! I paid a lot for it!

293
00:15:20,215 --> 00:15:21,215
Yes, Auntie.

294
00:15:25,817 --> 00:15:28,113
Why is it flying so high?

295
00:15:28,113 --> 00:15:30,588
I'm not feeling so good.

296
00:15:30,588 --> 00:15:34,061
Maybe I should start chanting.

297
00:15:34,061 --> 00:15:35,817
Sadhu.

298
00:15:35,817 --> 00:15:40,728
Sappe Satta Wisung Wisung Lakkhanathaya

299
00:15:40,728 --> 00:15:42,597
Tisārana na saha...

300
00:15:42,597 --> 00:15:43,667
Excuse me, Auntie.

301
00:15:44,301 --> 00:15:46,449
I’m sorry, but you can’t chant out loud.

302
00:15:46,449 --> 00:15:47,721
Why not, dear?

303
00:15:47,721 --> 00:15:50,118
Your voice is disturbing other passengers.

304
00:15:50,118 --> 00:15:51,744
I see…disturbing. I get that.

305
00:15:51,744 --> 00:15:54,498
But maybe everyone wants some good karma too!

306
00:15:54,498 --> 00:15:58,045
My heart’s racing, we’re so high up, I’m all anxious!

307
00:15:58,045 --> 00:16:01,479
Could you maybe save the merit-making for another day?

308
00:16:01,479 --> 00:16:02,950
So picky.

309
00:16:02,950 --> 00:16:06,381
If I can’t chant, then can someone turn down the air, please? I'm cold.

310
00:16:06,381 --> 00:16:09,333
The cabin temperature is set for the whole aircraft, Auntie.

311
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:10,169
So that can’t be done either?

312
00:16:10,169 --> 00:16:11,169
I’m afraid not.

313
00:16:11,641 --> 00:16:14,629
What? I can’t do anything on this plane. I'm going to lie down then.

314
00:16:14,629 --> 00:16:15,629
That’s good, Auntie.

315
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:23,784
Auntie, what are you doing?

316
00:16:23,784 --> 00:16:25,289
Well, I’m lying down, dear.

317
00:16:25,289 --> 00:16:27,483
You told me to rest, so here I am, resting!

318
00:16:27,483 --> 00:16:29,152
This is the perfect spot for a nap!

319
00:16:29,152 --> 00:16:31,221
You’re really making yourself at home here, Auntie.

320
00:16:31,221 --> 00:16:32,290
This seat is hard as a rock.

321
00:16:32,290 --> 00:16:34,082
I’m old. My back hurts.

322
00:16:34,082 --> 00:16:36,191
Stretching my legs like this feels so much better.

323
00:16:36,191 --> 00:16:38,099
I’m sorry, Auntie, but you can’t lie down here.

324
00:16:38,099 --> 00:16:40,600
Why not? What now, dear?

325
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,593
You have to stay seated, Auntie.

326
00:16:42,593 --> 00:16:44,747
The seat is too hard! I can’t stretch my legs out!

327
00:16:44,747 --> 00:16:46,854
But according to the regulations, it’s really not safe.

328
00:16:46,854 --> 00:16:48,400
If we hit turbulence,

329
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,400
you could get thrown into the ceiling, Auntie.

330
00:16:53,191 --> 00:16:54,700
That is scary, now that you mention it. Right, sweetie?

331
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:57,011
Yes. Let me help you tidy up. Okay.

332
00:16:57,011 --> 00:16:59,011
Thanks, dear. Please take care of it.

333
00:17:13,318 --> 00:17:17,318
Auntie, why’d you open that? I’m trying to sleep!

334
00:17:17,590 --> 00:17:21,590
I’m feeling stuffy! I want to look out far away.

335
00:17:21,825 --> 00:17:24,254
I feel like I’m going to throw up.

336
00:17:24,254 --> 00:17:27,254
If you’re going to throw up, please do it in the restroom. I’m trying to sleep here!

337
00:17:30,367 --> 00:17:34,367
Kids these days…no compassion for the elderly at all!

338
00:17:38,317 --> 00:17:42,317
Auntie, why’d you open that?

339
00:17:42,545 --> 00:17:45,781
Come on, dear. Let’s just go fifty-fifty.

340
00:17:45,781 --> 00:17:47,889
Half for you, half for me, yeah?

341
00:17:47,889 --> 00:17:49,199
Whatever you want, Auntie.

342
00:17:49,199 --> 00:17:50,199
Thanks, sweetie.

343
00:17:50,909 --> 00:17:52,856
I really can’t hold it anymore, I think I’m going to throw up.

344
00:17:52,856 --> 00:17:54,856
Right, dear? You agree with me, don’t you?

345
00:18:13,644 --> 00:18:15,644
There! There it is! Oh wow, this is fun!

346
00:18:30,152 --> 00:18:31,152
Auntie,

347
00:18:31,267 --> 00:18:33,262
please don’t turn the light on and off like that.

348
00:18:33,262 --> 00:18:35,409
Oh? I can’t?

349
00:18:35,409 --> 00:18:37,563
No, Auntie. It disturbs other passengers.

350
00:18:38,038 --> 00:18:39,072
But I think it’s kind of fun!

351
00:18:39,072 --> 00:18:40,866
No no, it’s really not allowed, Auntie.

352
00:18:40,866 --> 00:18:41,936
Alright, alright, alright.

353
00:18:41,936 --> 00:18:42,244
Okay.

354
00:18:42,244 --> 00:18:42,950
Turning it off now.

355
00:18:42,950 --> 00:18:43,950
Yes, thank you.

356
00:18:52,819 --> 00:18:56,819
Oh! A phone? Perfect!

357
00:18:57,285 --> 00:18:59,285
I don’t even know if Boy’s eaten yet...

358
00:19:01,516 --> 00:19:02,516
Hello? Boy?

359
00:19:03,505 --> 00:19:04,505
Boy!

360
00:19:05,377 --> 00:19:06,377
Boy!

361
00:19:06,852 --> 00:19:08,679
Can you hear me, sweetie?

362
00:19:08,679 --> 00:19:09,713
Have you eaten yet? You there?

363
00:19:09,713 --> 00:19:11,179
Excuse me, Auntie.

364
00:19:11,179 --> 00:19:12,851
You can’t use that phone.

365
00:19:12,851 --> 00:19:14,397
What? Why not?

366
00:19:14,397 --> 00:19:16,945
Can’t I just call my grandson real quick?

367
00:19:16,945 --> 00:19:20,021
I’m sorry, Auntie. That phone is for in-flight use only.

368
00:19:20,021 --> 00:19:21,096
So I can’t call outside at all?

369
00:19:21,096 --> 00:19:21,644
No, you can’t.

370
00:19:21,644 --> 00:19:22,644
Not at all, Auntie.

371
00:19:24,719 --> 00:19:25,427
Oh really, dear?

372
00:19:25,427 --> 00:19:26,061
Yes.

373
00:19:26,061 --> 00:19:27,732
Why is everything forbidden these days, huh?

374
00:19:27,732 --> 00:19:29,967
It’s the airline’s policy, Auntie.

375
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:30,967
For everyone’s safety.

376
00:19:32,358 --> 00:19:34,358
Please return to your seat, Auntie.

377
00:19:40,226 --> 00:19:43,379
Sweetie, where’s the bathroom?

378
00:19:43,379 --> 00:19:44,379
Over there, Auntie.

379
00:19:50,806 --> 00:19:52,436
Let me go first, okay? I'm old.

380
00:19:52,436 --> 00:19:55,668
Come on, Auntie. I’ve got a stomachache too! Please let me go first!

381
00:19:55,668 --> 00:19:57,668
Sweetie, no compassion for the elderly, huh?

382
00:20:01,619 --> 00:20:03,619
What? Auntie!

383
00:20:07,134 --> 00:20:08,134
Girls!

384
00:20:08,448 --> 00:20:09,448
Flight attendants!

385
00:20:10,555 --> 00:20:12,388
Where’s the flight attendant?

386
00:20:12,388 --> 00:20:14,579
Auntie, are you alright?

387
00:20:16,339 --> 00:20:17,332
Hmm? Auntie, are you okay?

388
00:20:17,332 --> 00:20:18,682
It’s everywhere…

389
00:20:19,155 --> 00:20:20,623
There’s no water dipper in here?

390
00:20:20,623 --> 00:20:21,887
Can someone bring me a dipper, please?

391
00:20:21,887 --> 00:20:23,075
We don’t have a dipper, Auntie.

392
00:20:23,075 --> 00:20:23,707
A bottle’s fine too.

393
00:20:23,707 --> 00:20:25,019
I’ll fill it up with water and pour it to clean.

394
00:20:25,019 --> 00:20:26,330
Auntie, I think it’s best if you press the button first.

395
00:20:26,330 --> 00:20:26,798
Yes.

396
00:20:26,798 --> 00:20:27,798
The blue one there.

397
00:20:28,344 --> 00:20:32,344
What the heck! No dipper? What kind of place is this?

398
00:20:33,298 --> 00:20:34,605
Sky!

399
00:20:34,605 --> 00:20:35,913
You press it!

400
00:20:35,913 --> 00:20:37,664
What? You do it!

401
00:20:37,664 --> 00:20:38,969
No, you!

402
00:20:38,969 --> 00:20:40,399
No way, you!

403
00:20:40,399 --> 00:20:40,790
Alright, how about this?

404
00:20:40,790 --> 00:20:41,781
You’re closer to the door than I am.

405
00:20:41,781 --> 00:20:43,338
No, listen to my offer...

406
00:20:43,338 --> 00:20:45,764
I’ll make another hidden account to boost the views of your video.

407
00:20:45,764 --> 00:20:48,235
the video of your pink bag that you’re selling.

408
00:20:48,235 --> 00:20:49,235
Deal?

409
00:20:50,308 --> 00:20:51,308
Fine. I’ll do it.

410
00:20:51,455 --> 00:20:52,455
Okay, go.

411
00:20:52,883 --> 00:20:54,883
One, two, three!

412
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,869
Did Auntie eat stinky stir-fried veggies or something?

413
00:21:13,869 --> 00:21:15,869
It reeks like crazy in here!

414
00:21:22,978 --> 00:21:24,615
So you really went and stormed into the Glamorous office...

415
00:21:24,615 --> 00:21:26,441
and on top of that, you assaulted someone too!

416
00:21:26,441 --> 00:21:28,071
Don’t you think that’s a bit much, Madam?

417
00:21:28,071 --> 00:21:31,141
I don’t know. Tid-Gift’s one of Glamorous’ people.

418
00:21:31,141 --> 00:21:33,135
So I count her as my enemy too.

419
00:21:33,135 --> 00:21:34,848
But what you did, Madam Porn, was way too much.

420
00:21:34,848 --> 00:21:37,877
Seriously, what if you’d done something worse today

421
00:21:37,877 --> 00:21:40,347
and ended up in prison for life?

422
00:21:40,347 --> 00:21:42,222
Never seeing the sun again?

423
00:21:42,222 --> 00:21:43,934
I’d be devastated, honestly.

424
00:21:43,934 --> 00:21:45,846
You need to think things through, Madam.

425
00:21:45,846 --> 00:21:48,872
Honestly, what I did today? That was nothing.

426
00:21:48,872 --> 00:21:51,872
I could’ve done a lot more.

427
00:21:53,626 --> 00:21:56,057
Madam, if you keep this up,

428
00:21:56,057 --> 00:21:58,804
the whole plan we’ve been working on? It’s going to fall apart.

429
00:21:58,804 --> 00:22:01,395
And all of us, we’re all going down with it.

430
00:22:01,395 --> 00:22:04,785
Then let it all fall apart!

431
00:22:04,785 --> 00:22:08,786
Someone like me, Madam Porn, I’m not going down alone.

432
00:22:13,855 --> 00:22:15,041
What are you waiting for, Siri?

433
00:22:15,041 --> 00:22:16,041
Laugh with me.

434
00:22:18,912 --> 00:22:19,912
Fake.

435
00:22:23,423 --> 00:22:24,423
Louder.

436
00:22:34,291 --> 00:22:35,291
Hurts, doesn’t it?

437
00:22:36,479 --> 00:22:37,479
It does.

438
00:22:39,030 --> 00:22:41,030
If this is how it’s going to be, I’m resigning.

439
00:22:43,585 --> 00:22:46,218
You can quit if you want, Kreetha.

440
00:22:46,218 --> 00:22:51,718
But the one stuck with debt will be your mother!

441
00:23:03,689 --> 00:23:04,841
How is it?

442
00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:06,841
Good? I just got slapped, you know.

443
00:23:09,626 --> 00:23:10,626
Right...

444
00:23:11,775 --> 00:23:14,652
Who even is that crazy Auntie?

445
00:23:14,652 --> 00:23:16,688
Why does she want to know so much about us?

446
00:23:16,688 --> 00:23:19,881
Let me guess, definitely bipolar.

447
00:23:19,881 --> 00:23:21,881
One minute she’s Pam, next she’s Madam Porn.

448
00:23:23,306 --> 00:23:25,306
Doesn’t she get confused being herself?

449
00:23:27,257 --> 00:23:28,257
True. Very true.

450
00:23:29,807 --> 00:23:31,843
But what I’m even more curious about is...

451
00:23:31,843 --> 00:23:34,836
how the hell does she know so much about us?

452
00:23:34,836 --> 00:23:40,141
She even knows you're the one-night Casanova.

453
00:23:40,141 --> 00:23:43,209
Well, what do you think? She nailed it, didn’t she?

454
00:23:43,209 --> 00:23:47,040
Yeah, and she also knows you’re a party girl on the prowl.

455
00:23:47,040 --> 00:23:49,040
Right? That’s true too.

456
00:23:50,155 --> 00:23:52,189
Wait, hold on! Are you trying to scold me?

457
00:23:52,189 --> 00:23:53,825
So are you gonna treat the wound or what?

458
00:23:53,825 --> 00:23:57,376
I am treating it. What, you think I’m out here golfing?

459
00:23:57,376 --> 00:23:58,376
Sit still.

460
00:23:58,488 --> 00:23:59,488
Fine.

461
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:03,786
Damn, that slap packed a punch. It's all bruised.

462
00:24:03,786 --> 00:24:05,932
Damn, how bad is it?

463
00:24:05,932 --> 00:24:07,932
Am I disfigured?

464
00:24:09,689 --> 00:24:10,689
Are you done yet?

465
00:24:14,884 --> 00:24:17,753
Hey, what are you laughing at?

466
00:24:17,753 --> 00:24:19,463
Nothing. Nothing at all.

467
00:24:19,463 --> 00:24:21,659
Well, I’ve got another appointment. I’m heading out.

468
00:24:21,659 --> 00:24:22,812
You’re seriously going now?

469
00:24:22,812 --> 00:24:26,208
Yeah. I was swiping and found

470
00:24:26,208 --> 00:24:29,923
a hot Asian guy, cute face, big chest, total heart-throb.

471
00:24:29,923 --> 00:24:33,117
So I’m gonna hit a cafe nearby.

472
00:24:33,117 --> 00:24:34,117
Right now?

473
00:24:34,187 --> 00:24:37,187
Yes. What? Are you afraid I’ll get harassed or something?

474
00:24:38,944 --> 00:24:42,931
No, just…I think maybe don’t go.

475
00:24:42,931 --> 00:24:45,521
I’m going. I want to get sexually harassed.

476
00:24:45,521 --> 00:24:45,954
Bye!

477
00:24:45,954 --> 00:24:49,259
Tid-Gift...

478
00:24:49,259 --> 00:24:53,259
What I’m afraid of is that he’ll laugh in your face, you idiot.

479
00:25:01,927 --> 00:25:04,961
Here you go, Auntie. I’m serving your meal now. I’ll set it down for you.

480
00:25:04,961 --> 00:25:08,350
Wait, wait, sweetie. Is this tiny box all I get?

481
00:25:08,350 --> 00:25:09,350
Yes, Auntie.

482
00:25:09,696 --> 00:25:10,696
Can I order more?

483
00:25:11,211 --> 00:25:12,211
Absolutely, Auntie.

484
00:25:12,442 --> 00:25:13,831
This won’t be enough for me, I’m telling you.

485
00:25:13,831 --> 00:25:15,376
Here you go, you can order more from the menu.

486
00:25:15,376 --> 00:25:16,845
Oh really, dear? Oh!

487
00:25:16,845 --> 00:25:20,631
Give me that, sweetie. I’ll take one burnt cheesecake, please.

488
00:25:20,631 --> 00:25:21,182
Sure.

489
00:25:21,182 --> 00:25:23,455
Spaghetti. Macaroni.

490
00:25:24,034 --> 00:25:25,586
And pizza.

491
00:25:25,787 --> 00:25:26,573
Don’t mind me.

492
00:25:26,573 --> 00:25:26,761
Of course.

493
00:25:26,761 --> 00:25:28,797
Do you have sticky rice in bamboo?

494
00:25:28,797 --> 00:25:30,866
I’m afraid you’ll have to get that from Nong Mon Market.

495
00:25:30,866 --> 00:25:31,852
So you don't have it?

496
00:25:31,852 --> 00:25:32,278
We don’t have it, Auntie.

497
00:25:32,278 --> 00:25:33,473
Alright then, just this will do.

498
00:25:33,473 --> 00:25:34,345
That’s quite a lot, Auntie.

499
00:25:34,744 --> 00:25:35,015
I’m hungry!

500
00:25:35,015 --> 00:25:37,209
Wouldn’t it be better to wait for the buffet?

501
00:25:37,209 --> 00:25:38,682
Hey now, are you being sarcastic?

502
00:25:38,682 --> 00:25:40,026
Just teasing.

503
00:25:40,026 --> 00:25:43,137
Just teasing, Auntie.

504
00:25:43,137 --> 00:25:45,167
Enjoy your meal, Auntie.

505
00:25:45,645 --> 00:25:47,071
So polite.

506
00:25:47,071 --> 00:25:48,503
Everyone’s so kind here.

507
00:25:48,503 --> 00:25:51,452
Whatever I order, I get it all, huh, sweetie?

508
00:25:51,452 --> 00:25:52,884
Unlimited, right?

509
00:25:52,884 --> 00:25:55,550
Um...what do you mean “unlimited”?

510
00:25:55,550 --> 00:25:57,820
I ordered a bunch and got it all.

511
00:25:57,820 --> 00:25:58,605
It’s free, right?

512
00:25:58,605 --> 00:26:00,718
It’s not free, Auntie.

513
00:26:00,718 --> 00:26:03,833
The menu you ordered cost extra.

514
00:26:03,833 --> 00:26:07,461
They’re not included in the complimentary set.

515
00:26:07,461 --> 00:26:08,132
Oh, really?

516
00:26:08,132 --> 00:26:08,765
Yes.

517
00:26:08,765 --> 00:26:10,992
So that means...I have to pay for it?

518
00:26:10,992 --> 00:26:11,825
Yes, Auntie.

519
00:26:11,825 --> 00:26:12,980
Can I return it then?

520
00:26:12,980 --> 00:26:13,647
Uh...no.

521
00:26:13,647 --> 00:26:14,556
No, Auntie.

522
00:26:14,556 --> 00:26:15,461
No. No returns, I’m afraid.

523
00:26:15,461 --> 00:26:17,008
But I haven’t even opened it yet. Can I return it?

524
00:26:17,008 --> 00:26:18,685
Still no, Auntie.

525
00:26:18,685 --> 00:26:21,949
That’ll be...3,899 baht.

526
00:26:21,949 --> 00:26:24,221
What the hell? 3,899?

527
00:26:24,221 --> 00:26:26,532
Are you kidding me?! This is like a Chinese banquet table!

528
00:26:26,532 --> 00:26:29,598
Will you be paying by cash or credit card?

529
00:26:29,598 --> 00:26:31,675
I don’t have a card. I only have cash.

530
00:26:31,675 --> 00:26:32,544
That’s fine.

531
00:26:32,544 --> 00:26:35,774
Can I get a discount? It’s way too much. So expensive!

532
00:26:35,774 --> 00:26:37,532
I’m sorry, we can’t do that.

533
00:26:37,532 --> 00:26:41,532
Sweetie, you want it? I’ll resell it to you, 60 baht per box.

534
00:26:43,322 --> 00:26:45,475
You don’t look full, you really don’t.

535
00:26:45,475 --> 00:26:46,864
Wanna buy some, sweetie?

536
00:26:46,864 --> 00:26:49,737
Auntie, just eat it yourself, trust me.

537
00:26:49,737 --> 00:26:53,738
Wanna buy one? Just 60 baht, sweetie.

538
00:26:56,562 --> 00:26:57,755
Fine, I’ll take them all.

539
00:26:57,755 --> 00:26:59,424
So you’ll be paying cash, Auntie?

540
00:26:59,424 --> 00:27:00,571
Yes, cash it is, dear.

541
00:27:00,571 --> 00:27:01,198
Alright. Count it, okay?

542
00:27:01,198 --> 00:27:02,198
Help me count it.

543
00:27:05,632 --> 00:27:08,268
Will it be enough? Help me count, dear.

544
00:27:08,268 --> 00:27:11,664
Here, bring your hand over.

545
00:27:12,329 --> 00:27:15,006
All I’ve got left are coins now. I’m broke. You count it.

546
00:27:15,006 --> 00:27:16,918
Fifty satang, ten satang…make sure it adds up, girl.

547
00:27:16,918 --> 00:27:20,514
Sky, should we just pay for Auntie so this can be over?

548
00:27:20,514 --> 00:27:22,147
No, I haven’t even gotten my paycheck yet.

549
00:27:22,147 --> 00:27:25,693
If we wait till we land, we’ll still be counting.

550
00:27:25,693 --> 00:27:27,923
Better take what we can get than get nothing at all.

551
00:27:27,923 --> 00:27:29,878
Auntie, do you have anything else? Please check.

552
00:27:29,878 --> 00:27:31,024
Wait, let me look.

553
00:27:31,024 --> 00:27:32,822
Oh! One more bill! Here!

554
00:27:32,822 --> 00:27:34,933
A thousand-baht note works, or hundreds.

555
00:27:34,933 --> 00:27:35,933
I’ve got nothing left, dear.

556
00:27:36,759 --> 00:27:39,068
Wait, does my Mom really owe you money, Madam Porn?

557
00:27:39,068 --> 00:27:41,183
Do I look like your Mom, Kreetha? Huh?

558
00:27:41,183 --> 00:27:43,183
If you wanna know, why don’t you call and ask her?

559
00:27:47,573 --> 00:27:49,573
Hello, Mom? Do you really owe Madam Porn money?

560
00:27:51,407 --> 00:27:55,407
Hello, are you Kreetha’s mother?

561
00:27:55,634 --> 00:27:58,788
My name is Porn. I’m Kreetha’s boss.

562
00:27:58,788 --> 00:28:01,776
I don’t believe you. This is a scam call, isn’t it?

563
00:28:01,776 --> 00:28:05,246
Oh no, I really am Kreetha’s boss!

564
00:28:05,246 --> 00:28:09,246
By the way, do you have any outstanding COD parcels awaiting payment?

565
00:28:09,840 --> 00:28:11,512
Oops, not that.

566
00:28:11,512 --> 00:28:15,503
Sorry, my name is Porn. I truly am Kreetha’s boss.

567
00:28:15,503 --> 00:28:19,503
Ah, that’s a relief. I thought you were a scammer.

568
00:28:20,131 --> 00:28:22,716
So, are you busy right now?

569
00:28:22,716 --> 00:28:26,717
Oh, I’m running. Running up and down. I’m exhausted!

570
00:28:27,032 --> 00:28:29,699
Sounds tiring!

571
00:28:29,699 --> 00:28:35,893
Does your business happen to need additional funding right now?

572
00:28:35,893 --> 00:28:37,893
Oh, it really does, so much!

573
00:28:40,090 --> 00:28:45,882
Perfect! This year, Kreetha got a big bonus from the company.

574
00:28:45,882 --> 00:28:51,431
So he asked me to transfer a lump sum to help you out.

575
00:28:51,431 --> 00:28:55,432
Oh, what a wonderful child! Then I’ll take 100,000 baht, please.

576
00:28:55,586 --> 00:28:59,420
My business is really struggling. Go ahead and transfer it!

577
00:28:59,420 --> 00:29:02,165
Of course, I’ll take care of that for you.

578
00:29:02,165 --> 00:29:05,320
I’m just so happy for you, really...

579
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:07,320
having such a grateful son like Kreetha.

580
00:29:09,595 --> 00:29:11,866
Mom! Why would you do that?

581
00:29:11,866 --> 00:29:13,823
You’re making things harder for me again!

582
00:29:13,823 --> 00:29:17,010
What? Your boss offered the money herself!

583
00:29:17,010 --> 00:29:20,010
Anyway, I gotta go now. I have to chase down lottery numbers. Bye, Kreetha!

584
00:29:28,327 --> 00:29:30,597
I can't believe this…

585
00:29:30,597 --> 00:29:31,911
You really called my mom and tricked her

586
00:29:31,911 --> 00:29:33,977
just to make me work for you for the rest of my life?

587
00:29:33,977 --> 00:29:37,092
I’m sorry, Kreetha.

588
00:29:37,092 --> 00:29:41,092
But you see, in situations like this...it’s not about the method.

589
00:29:41,244 --> 00:29:43,758
It’s about the result.

590
00:29:43,758 --> 00:29:46,631
And right now, your mother’s in my debt.

591
00:29:46,631 --> 00:29:50,631
Unless…you’d rather have her come work it off herself.

592
00:29:52,624 --> 00:29:56,624
Well? All-New? Siri? What are you two sucking on?

593
00:29:57,058 --> 00:29:58,058
Aren’t you gonna say anything?

594
00:30:00,530 --> 00:30:01,530
A candy.

595
00:30:03,199 --> 00:30:04,199
A plum.

596
00:30:05,310 --> 00:30:09,310
This is exactly why you are so power-hungry and selfish.

597
00:30:09,382 --> 00:30:11,382
You know what? I’m done! I’m outta here!

598
00:30:16,134 --> 00:30:20,134
Madam, what are you sucking on? Don’t you have anything to say?

599
00:30:21,886 --> 00:30:22,886
A gooseberry.

600
00:30:24,036 --> 00:30:27,149
Seriously? No one’s gonna go after Kreetha?

601
00:30:27,149 --> 00:30:29,135
If you’re so worried about him,

602
00:30:29,135 --> 00:30:30,323
why don’t you go?

603
00:30:30,323 --> 00:30:31,511
I can’t, Madam.

604
00:30:31,511 --> 00:30:32,341
Why not?

605
00:30:32,341 --> 00:30:33,841
Because…you’re standing on my foot.

606
00:30:35,374 --> 00:30:36,374
Oh! Sorry.

607
00:30:37,769 --> 00:30:39,769
Kreetha! Kreetha!

608
00:30:56,997 --> 00:30:59,386
We’ve been flying for so long. When are we finally going to arrive?

609
00:30:59,386 --> 00:31:01,611
I'm getting really uncomfortable here.

610
00:31:01,611 --> 00:31:04,765
Hey, sweetie! Do you see it? Do you see it?

611
00:31:04,765 --> 00:31:06,318
Do you see my house roof down there?

612
00:31:06,318 --> 00:31:09,272
That one with the lines going through the middle, that’s the Sakae Krang River!

613
00:31:09,272 --> 00:31:11,063
We’re getting close to my house!

614
00:31:11,063 --> 00:31:13,535
Girls! Girls!

615
00:31:13,535 --> 00:31:15,206
Tell the driver to stop for me!

616
00:31:15,206 --> 00:31:16,800
Look, we’re about to pass my house!

617
00:31:16,800 --> 00:31:17,673
What is it, Auntie?

618
00:31:17,673 --> 00:31:20,021
My house! That’s my house roof! Do you see it? Do you?

619
00:31:20,021 --> 00:31:22,889
Go tell the driver to stop! I want to get off!

620
00:31:22,889 --> 00:31:24,271
You can’t get off here, Auntie.

621
00:31:24,271 --> 00:31:26,065
Why not? That’s my house down there!

622
00:31:26,065 --> 00:31:27,056
You really want to go, Auntie?

623
00:31:27,056 --> 00:31:27,883
Of course!

624
00:31:27,883 --> 00:31:29,716
Then go ahead and jump.

625
00:31:29,716 --> 00:31:32,430
Once you jump, you’ll land straight in the Sakae Krang River, right?

626
00:31:32,430 --> 00:31:32,786
Yes.

627
00:31:32,786 --> 00:31:36,662
Then just swim, swim, swim your way home, since your house is right by the river, huh?

628
00:31:36,662 --> 00:31:37,216
That’s right!

629
00:31:37,216 --> 00:31:38,604
Are you crazy, Auntie?

630
00:31:38,604 --> 00:31:40,879
You can’t just jump! What do you think this is, Charlie’s Angels?

631
00:31:40,879 --> 00:31:43,585
I'm fine! I just want to go home, sweetie!

632
00:31:43,585 --> 00:31:44,254
I’ll tell him myself!

633
00:31:44,254 --> 00:31:44,961
You can’t do that, Auntie.

634
00:31:44,961 --> 00:31:46,153
Driver! Driver!

635
00:31:46,153 --> 00:31:47,430
Driver, stop for me, please!

636
00:31:47,430 --> 00:31:49,905
It’s called the captain, Auntie. Not the driver.

637
00:31:49,905 --> 00:31:52,858
it's called Driver, if he drives the car, the boat, the plane...

638
00:31:52,860 --> 00:31:53,847
Hey! Driver!

639
00:31:54,444 --> 00:31:55,005
We’ve passed my house already!

640
00:31:55,005 --> 00:31:55,877
Please don’t disturb the captain.

641
00:31:55,877 --> 00:31:57,383
Back to your seat now, Auntie.

642
00:31:57,383 --> 00:31:58,383
It’s dangerous.

643
00:31:59,850 --> 00:32:02,320
Auntie, if we hit turbulence, it could be really dangerous.

644
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:03,232
Please go back to your seat.

645
00:32:03,232 --> 00:32:04,623
No! I want that driver to stop this plane!

646
00:32:04,623 --> 00:32:05,538
Driver! Stop the plane for me right now!

647
00:32:05,538 --> 00:32:06,807
Auntie, you really can’t!

648
00:32:06,807 --> 00:32:08,838
Please sit down, it’s very dangerous.

649
00:32:08,838 --> 00:32:09,838
Driver!

650
00:32:12,425 --> 00:32:13,425
Driver!

651
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:17,933
Auntie!

652
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:27,560
If you’ve got something to say, then say it. Stop sucking on that.

653
00:32:29,915 --> 00:32:31,701
It’s completely melted now.

654
00:32:31,701 --> 00:32:33,693
The reason I haven’t said anything...

655
00:32:33,693 --> 00:32:35,693
is because I hate seeing Mom like this.

656
00:32:42,206 --> 00:32:45,954
Mom…can you please stop being like this?

657
00:32:45,954 --> 00:32:49,664
I want my sweet, kind mom back, the one I used to know.

658
00:32:49,664 --> 00:32:53,664
All-New, you’ve seen it with your own eyes. All this time, I’ve been the one getting hurt.

659
00:32:54,692 --> 00:32:55,692
I’m done being the victim.

660
00:32:57,882 --> 00:33:00,668
I know what you’ve been through, Mom.

661
00:33:00,668 --> 00:33:02,855
But it’s still not too late to take a step back.

662
00:33:02,855 --> 00:33:05,048
I’ve come too far to back down now.

663
00:33:05,048 --> 00:33:07,048
Please trust me, Mom. Just try taking a step back.

664
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:10,760
Another step.

665
00:33:12,075 --> 00:33:13,075
A little more.

666
00:33:14,668 --> 00:33:16,668
I can't. All-New.

667
00:33:16,822 --> 00:33:17,822
Don’t bother, All-New.

668
00:33:18,811 --> 00:33:21,811
There’s no going back to who I was.

669
00:33:23,883 --> 00:33:27,883
If you can’t accept having a mom like me,

670
00:33:28,112 --> 00:33:30,112
then go ahead. Cut me out of your life.

671
00:33:48,309 --> 00:33:50,309
How can you say that, Mom?

672
00:34:27,105 --> 00:34:28,105
My whole body hurts.

673
00:34:34,819 --> 00:34:37,975
Don’t tell me…we all died?

674
00:34:37,975 --> 00:34:38,975
No way.

675
00:34:40,048 --> 00:34:41,114
I’m not dead yet!

676
00:34:41,114 --> 00:34:44,114
No… no…am I really dead?

677
00:34:51,949 --> 00:34:53,217
Did I die?

678
00:34:53,217 --> 00:34:57,217
You’re dead, Auntie. Lord Yama sent the two of us to take you to pay for your sins.

679
00:34:58,571 --> 00:35:01,321
I don’t have any sins! I’ve never done anything to anyone!

680
00:35:02,230 --> 00:35:04,020
Still lying, huh?

681
00:35:04,020 --> 00:35:05,731
We’ll cut out your tongue if you lie again.

682
00:35:05,731 --> 00:35:06,801
No, don’t cut my tongue!

683
00:35:06,801 --> 00:35:07,801
Don’t cut my tongue!

684
00:35:09,156 --> 00:35:11,147
Oh, now you’re scared.

685
00:35:11,147 --> 00:35:13,663
But what about when you disturbed and bothered everyone else?

686
00:35:13,663 --> 00:35:14,212
Huh?

687
00:35:14,212 --> 00:35:15,367
You created chaos for everyone.

688
00:35:15,367 --> 00:35:18,872
Let’s make her climb the thorn tree and stab her with spears!

689
00:35:18,872 --> 00:35:19,872
No! I’m scared!

690
00:35:21,302 --> 00:35:22,409
Please don’t do this to me!

691
00:35:22,409 --> 00:35:23,409
You don’t want to climb the thorn tree?

692
00:35:23,717 --> 00:35:24,717
Nope.

693
00:35:24,788 --> 00:35:25,788
Then pay up.

694
00:35:26,258 --> 00:35:27,011
Pay for what?

695
00:35:27,011 --> 00:35:28,647
For exorcise misfortune.

696
00:35:28,647 --> 00:35:29,647
Warding off bad karma?

697
00:35:29,722 --> 00:35:30,590
Exactly.

698
00:35:30,590 --> 00:35:31,590
Can I pay with money?

699
00:35:32,665 --> 00:35:34,334
I have money! I have money!

700
00:35:34,334 --> 00:35:37,039
Here, take it! Go on, take it all!

701
00:35:37,039 --> 00:35:38,866
All of it! Everything!

702
00:35:38,866 --> 00:35:41,137
You think that’s enough to cover your sins?

703
00:35:42,803 --> 00:35:44,238
There’s more?

704
00:35:44,238 --> 00:35:46,025
Talking during movies.

705
00:35:46,025 --> 00:35:47,933
Asking people when they’re getting married.

706
00:35:47,933 --> 00:35:49,600
Bragging about your kids and grandkids.

707
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:50,468
Cutting in line.

708
00:35:50,468 --> 00:35:52,785
Bullying strangers for being fat.

709
00:35:52,785 --> 00:35:55,539
Telling people they look ugly when you first meet them.

710
00:35:55,539 --> 00:35:57,608
Sticking your nose in other people’s business.

711
00:35:57,608 --> 00:35:58,608
That, too?

712
00:35:59,202 --> 00:36:02,431
And slapping that kid on Christmas!

713
00:36:02,431 --> 00:36:04,266
You’ve got a lot of sins, Auntie.

714
00:36:04,266 --> 00:36:05,335
What do I have to do, sweetie?

715
00:36:05,335 --> 00:36:06,889
What do I do?

716
00:36:06,889 --> 00:36:08,200
All sins…

717
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:09,200
can be washed away with cash.

718
00:36:11,192 --> 00:36:13,192
Yes! I can do that!

719
00:36:15,223 --> 00:36:15,773
Here! Take it all!

720
00:36:15,773 --> 00:36:18,773
I'm loaded, just take it! Wipe all of it away!

721
00:36:24,122 --> 00:36:26,552
Can I go to heaven now, sweetie?

722
00:36:26,552 --> 00:36:27,552
Stop crying first.

723
00:36:27,618 --> 00:36:29,618
Can I go now?

724
00:36:29,808 --> 00:36:30,808
No, you can’t.

725
00:36:40,547 --> 00:36:43,255
Hey! What the hell happened to you two?

726
00:36:43,255 --> 00:36:45,049
Why do you look like walking corpses?

727
00:36:45,049 --> 00:36:51,049
How could we not? We just had to deal with that Auntie.

728
00:36:51,075 --> 00:36:54,985
From takeoff to landing, I was this close to losing it.

729
00:36:54,985 --> 00:36:57,658
Seriously, every single crazy flight happens to you guys.

730
00:36:57,658 --> 00:37:00,246
Speaking of Auntie, that reminds me...

731
00:37:00,246 --> 00:37:04,246
guess who showed up to cause a scene at the office today?

732
00:37:04,273 --> 00:37:05,466
Can I not guess?

733
00:37:05,466 --> 00:37:06,774
Just tell us already.

734
00:37:06,774 --> 00:37:08,328
Okay, okay!

735
00:37:08,328 --> 00:37:12,328
The Auntie I mentioned? It was Pam, the one we met at the bar!

736
00:37:13,235 --> 00:37:17,235
But now she claims she’s not Pam, she’s Madam Porn!

737
00:37:18,271 --> 00:37:23,666
Wait. So Pam is Madam Porn, and Madam Porn is Pam?

738
00:37:23,666 --> 00:37:25,300
Somchai is Sompong’s brother,

739
00:37:25,300 --> 00:37:27,210
Sompong is Somying’s brother,

740
00:37:27,210 --> 00:37:28,800
Somying is Lamyong’s older sister,

741
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:30,433
Lamyong is Somsak’s younger sister,

742
00:37:30,433 --> 00:37:32,550
Somsak is Sky’s Dad, and Sky is...

743
00:37:32,550 --> 00:37:35,904
What the hell? What are you even saying?

744
00:37:35,904 --> 00:37:37,452
Now, I’m just completely confused.

745
00:37:37,452 --> 00:37:39,122
Forget you being confused,

746
00:37:39,122 --> 00:37:40,600
I am confused!

747
00:37:40,600 --> 00:37:42,876
And what did Madam Porn do?

748
00:37:42,876 --> 00:37:44,876
Look at Tid-Gift’s face. Just look!

749
00:37:45,587 --> 00:37:46,857
Honestly, they’re the same.

750
00:37:46,857 --> 00:37:48,612
The Auntie and Madam Porn...

751
00:37:48,612 --> 00:37:52,007
If you’re near them, you either get hurt…or you die.

752
00:37:52,007 --> 00:37:55,397
The stuff we’ve been through...

753
00:37:55,397 --> 00:37:58,948
You know what? Maybe we should go do some good deeds for the elderly.

754
00:37:58,948 --> 00:37:59,695
Yeah.

755
00:37:59,695 --> 00:38:00,649
How do we do that though?

756
00:38:00,649 --> 00:38:02,758
Set a forest hermit free?

757
00:38:02,758 --> 00:38:04,758
I’m sending Shujok into Teeyai shop.

758
00:38:05,791 --> 00:38:07,384
Alright. Let’s go.

759
00:38:07,384 --> 00:38:07,934
Like, now?

760
00:38:07,934 --> 00:38:10,209
Yes. Go!

761
00:38:10,209 --> 00:38:11,285
Wait, I didn’t even stop the bleeding yet.

762
00:38:11,285 --> 00:38:12,285
Alright, fine!

763
00:38:20,114 --> 00:38:22,222
Kreetha, listen.

764
00:38:22,222 --> 00:38:24,095
Madam Porn...

765
00:38:24,095 --> 00:38:26,095
Kreetha, well, Madam Porn...

766
00:38:28,564 --> 00:38:29,564
Madam Porn...

767
00:38:31,118 --> 00:38:32,118
Well...

768
00:38:32,393 --> 00:38:35,145
Kreetha, stop and listen to me first!

769
00:38:35,145 --> 00:38:37,017
This isn't a scene from an Indian movie.

770
00:38:37,017 --> 00:38:39,485
Stop it right there, did Madam Porn send you to patch things up with me?

771
00:38:39,485 --> 00:38:41,837
It's not like that, Kreetha. Listen to me first.

772
00:38:41,837 --> 00:38:44,992
I'm not going to listen to you. Look at what she's done!

773
00:38:44,992 --> 00:38:48,067
She's done her hair quite well today.

774
00:38:48,067 --> 00:38:49,067
But she didn't get a new haircut.

775
00:38:49,656 --> 00:38:52,846
It's not funny, Siri. Madam Porn tricked my Mom.

776
00:38:52,846 --> 00:38:54,846
Hey, Kreetha.

777
00:39:01,357 --> 00:39:02,357
Well, she's not stopping.

778
00:39:04,751 --> 00:39:07,863
Kreetha, let me ask you this...

779
00:39:07,863 --> 00:39:08,651
About Madam Porn?

780
00:39:08,651 --> 00:39:11,085
No, about you! Would you stop walking around?

781
00:39:11,085 --> 00:39:13,517
Aren't you tired?

782
00:39:13,517 --> 00:39:14,634
Well, I'm mad.

783
00:39:14,634 --> 00:39:15,634
Listen to me.

784
00:39:18,351 --> 00:39:19,351
Madam Porn...

785
00:39:27,341 --> 00:39:31,341
Whoa! Would you stop it already?

786
00:39:34,296 --> 00:39:37,563
If you're mad at Madam Porn, I don’t blame you.

787
00:39:37,563 --> 00:39:41,763
If I were in your shoes, I’d be mad too. I don’t agree with what Madam Porn did..

788
00:39:42,597 --> 00:39:45,474
The way she handled it, it wasn’t right.

789
00:39:45,474 --> 00:39:49,474
But I know what she’s been through. That’s why she acted the way she did.

790
00:39:52,386 --> 00:39:53,577
Really, Siri?

791
00:39:53,577 --> 00:39:54,851
Yes, really.

792
00:39:54,851 --> 00:39:57,244
I’ve been with Madam Porn since the very beginning.

793
00:39:57,244 --> 00:40:01,111
She built Porn Airline with her bare hands, gave it everything she had.

794
00:40:01,111 --> 00:40:05,179
She fought her way up and built the whole thing all by herself.

795
00:40:05,179 --> 00:40:09,180
And one day, it all crashed back down to rock bottom…

796
00:40:09,529 --> 00:40:11,529
Just like what you saw, Kreetha.

797
00:40:13,923 --> 00:40:16,355
Please, try to understand her.

798
00:40:16,355 --> 00:40:20,355
She was bullied by rival airlines nonstop.

799
00:40:21,343 --> 00:40:25,344
And honestly, I don’t think Glamourous Airlines is all that great either.

800
00:40:27,012 --> 00:40:31,012
This is what turned Madam Porn into who she is today, Kreetha.

801
00:40:32,526 --> 00:40:34,198
You’re right, Siri.

802
00:40:34,198 --> 00:40:39,198
If you understand her, then go back and work with her again.

803
00:40:39,466 --> 00:40:41,466
Please. I’m asking you.

804
00:40:47,143 --> 00:40:50,651
Kreetha, don’t you remember?

805
00:40:50,651 --> 00:40:55,651
Back when you were struggling, wasn’t it Madam Porn who stepped in and helped you?

806
00:40:57,162 --> 00:41:01,162
Come on, go back and work with her, Kreetha.

807
00:41:04,549 --> 00:41:07,816
I get what you’re feeling.

808
00:41:07,816 --> 00:41:10,923
Nah, I was just thinking about what to eat. I’m starving.

809
00:41:10,923 --> 00:41:13,391
What the hell, I’ve been talking all this time!

810
00:41:13,391 --> 00:41:15,391
Why didn’t you just say so? I would’ve ordered you something already!

811
00:41:17,504 --> 00:41:21,504
So...are you saying you’ll go back to work with Madam Porn?

812
00:41:26,892 --> 00:41:30,892
Fine. But I’m only doing it for you, Siri.

813
00:41:31,763 --> 00:41:34,077
That’s what I’m talking about, kid!

814
00:41:34,077 --> 00:41:38,077
Come on, sit. What do you want to eat? It’s on me.

815
00:41:39,464 --> 00:41:41,940
You little brat. Took forever to win you over.

816
00:41:41,940 --> 00:41:43,015
Siri...

817
00:41:43,015 --> 00:41:45,082
Go ahead and order. Whatever you want.

818
00:41:45,082 --> 00:41:48,082
Hey, come here! Bring us the menu!

819
00:41:57,191 --> 00:41:59,418
Oww, sweetie, help me out a bit.

820
00:41:59,418 --> 00:42:01,969
Oh my god, I’ve got a cramp in my leg!

821
00:42:01,969 --> 00:42:02,969
Do you fly often?

822
00:42:04,123 --> 00:42:05,879
So many rules…If I’d known, I wouldn’t have come.

823
00:42:05,879 --> 00:42:06,879
I’m good. All good.

824
00:42:10,833 --> 00:42:11,533
My mouth’s twitching.

825
00:42:14,703 --> 00:42:16,054
It hurts, doesn’t it?

826
00:42:16,054 --> 00:42:17,054
Yes.

827
00:42:18,570 --> 00:42:19,481
Can I switch hands?

828
00:42:19,481 --> 00:42:20,348
Go ahead.

829
00:42:20,348 --> 00:42:21,143
I quit.

830
00:42:21,143 --> 00:42:23,492
You can quit if you want to...All...

831
00:42:23,492 --> 00:42:24,492
“All-New”?

832
00:42:25,761 --> 00:42:26,586
This is preserved plum, right?

833
00:42:26,586 --> 00:42:27,141
Here, plum.

834
00:42:27,141 --> 00:42:27,818
This is plum.

835
00:42:27,818 --> 00:42:29,818
It’s gooseberry for me. Here, I’ll hold it.

836
00:42:30,291 --> 00:42:31,291
I’d rather have plum.

837
00:42:32,518 --> 00:42:33,667
What are you even sucking on?

838
00:42:33,667 --> 00:42:34,667
No one’s gonna say anything?

839
00:42:35,776 --> 00:42:36,776
Plum.

840
00:42:43,450 --> 00:42:43,950
She's drooling.

841
00:42:44,439 --> 00:42:46,439
Auntie!

842
00:42:49,146 --> 00:42:51,146
Auntie!

843
00:42:54,058 --> 00:42:56,058
Auntie!

844
00:42:57,448 --> 00:42:59,448
Hey, wait! Hey!

845
00:43:07,759 --> 00:43:10,759
Mumbling through food, so disrespectful!

846
00:43:11,473 --> 00:43:13,473
Okay, cut! That’s a wrap! Great job.

847
00:43:16,830 --> 00:43:17,830
He's into dramatic stuff.

848
00:43:21,423 --> 00:43:25,423
Auntie, you're dead. The reaper came for us, wait no, no!

849
00:43:26,613 --> 00:43:32,329
He's Sky's brother. Sky, do you know Ninew?

850
00:43:32,329 --> 00:43:33,329
What?

851
00:43:33,877 --> 00:43:34,877
What?

852
00:43:35,508 --> 00:43:36,455
What?

853
00:43:36,455 --> 00:43:37,455
Hey, it’s possible, okay?

854
00:43:43,929 --> 00:43:47,516
I want you two to stir up some chaos on this flight.

855
00:43:47,516 --> 00:43:51,025
Or better yet...cause a full-blown tragedy.

856
00:43:51,025 --> 00:43:53,180
Even if Madam Porn told you to trigger a tragedy,

857
00:43:53,180 --> 00:43:54,371
Don’t go killing anyone, alright?

858
00:43:54,371 --> 00:43:57,638
Someone on this damn plane stole from me! They took my necklace!

859
00:43:57,638 --> 00:43:58,638
Please stay calm. Where did you last see it?

860
00:43:59,075 --> 00:44:01,275
I’m giving you my ultimate move.

861
00:44:02,944 --> 00:44:03,944
So we'll blow up this plane?

862
